snippet: The authorities said there were no reports of injuries or serious damage from the quake, which the United States Geological Survey said had a preliminary magnitude of 6.9.
abstract: Chilean authorities say there are no reports of injuries or serious damage following 6.9 earthquake that occurred in Pacific ocean, near coastal city of Coquimbo.
lead_paragraph: The authorities said there were no reports of injuries or serious damage from the quake, which the United States Geological Survey said had a preliminary magnitude of 6.9.

headline.print_headline: The Americas; Chile: Powerful Quake in Pacific
